FBIS3-18074 "drweu039aa_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS West Reacts to NATO's Downing of Serb Aircraft Spanish Troops To Join Multinational Brigade LD2502230694 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 2000 GMT 25 Feb 94 LD2502230694 Madrid TVE Internacional Television Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] The introduction of the cease-fire in Bosnia has brought about the creation of a mixed brigade of UN forces, which the Spanish battalion will join. The brigade initially will be commanded by a British general and will also include Canadian, British, and Malaysian troops. Its essential mission will be to reopen the River Neretva route.
